In addition, the total number of complete ballots may be counted if there is a difference between the alleged winner and the second-place winner, which is equal to or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the meeting an express request is made by the party or coalition chairman, who is the second of those candidates.
The vote count may also take place in its entirety if it is established, after completion of the proper calculation, that the difference between the prospective winner and the candidate in the second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided that an express request is made by a representative of the party whose candidate has become second. In this case, the electoral packages which have been subjected to a partial count would be excluded.
