He stressed that the investigation began at the sport site of Cuauhtémoc (in the West of the Federal State of Mexico) and continued since 8 October at the sports site of Nezahualcóylt (in the East of the Federal State of Mexico).
If the target of 500 to 600 investigators has been achieved, the study will continue at the sport site of Independencia (in the south of the capital district) and at the one of Morelos (in the north of the capital district).
He explained that the aim of the study was to identify the factors and the role of genetics in the development of obesity and to identify the risk factors of Mexican children and adolescents to prevent chronic degenerative diseases.
On the occasion of the World Day of Diabetes, he stated that it is intended that three thousand children and young people between the ages of six and 14 should complete the nutrition-related questionnaires under the supervision of their parents.
You will also be asked questions about their physical activity and their family history of disease in order to control risk factors that could result in diabetes or kidney failure.
